description: Swedish Stirling AB engages in the production and solutions for generating electricity. The company is headquartered in Vaestra Froelunda, Vastra Gotalands and currently employs 43 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2016-11-28. The firm offers a variety of solutions enabling power generation. Its engine can handle a wide range of fuels, such as industrial residual and flare gases and convert them into electrical energy.
